                  </hi>. I live with John Saunders, a cheesemonger, in King's-road, Chelsea. On the evening of the 22nd of September, in con<lb></lb>sequence of what Dixon told me, I missed a piece of bacon—I pursued and caught the prisoner, I brought him back, but could not find the bacon—I said, "Perhaps you have <hi rend="italic">chucked</hi> it over Mr. Wild's gate"—I went back, and could not find it—I then took off his hat, and found this bacon in it.</p>
